[{"id":"VR876706","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a side view and a front view. In the side view, three objects are shown on a horizontal surface. The leftmost object is a laser, from which a dashed horizontal line with an arrow pointing horizontally to the right extends toward the second object, which is a vertical screen with a slit. The distance between the laser and the screen with a slit is labeled D sub L S, end sub. The dashed line continues horizontally to the right toward the third object, which is a vertical viewing screen. The distance between the screen with a slit and the viewing screen is labeled D sub S V, end sub. The front view shows an enlarged view of the viewing screen, represented by a black square. Along a horizontal line through the square’s center a wide central white band is shown, with three smaller white bands shown to the left and right of the central band. Each band is separated by a small blank black space. Dashed vertical lines extend downward from the blank black space immediately to the left of the white band to the left of the central band, and from the blank black space immediately to the right of the white band to the right of the central band. The distance between these lines is x.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876706.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A laser beam is directed through a screen with a narrow vertical slit, forming a pattern that can be viewed on a second screen, as shown in the figure. The laser produces light of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda\"><math alttext=\"lambda\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>λ</mi></math></span></span> and is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub L S, end sub\"><math alttext=\"D sub L S, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>LS</mtext></msub></math></span></span> from the slit. The slit is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub S V, end sub\"><math alttext=\"D sub S V, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>SV</mtext></msub></math></span></span> from the viewing screen. On the viewing screen, the two dark fringes indicated in the front view in the figure are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span> apart. What is the approximate width of the slit?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876706_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda times D sub S V, end sub, and denominator x\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda times D sub S V, end sub, and denominator x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>SV</mtext></msub></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 4 lambda times D sub S V, end sub, and denominator x\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 4 lambda times D sub S V, end sub, and denominator x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>SV</mtext></msub></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda, times open parenthesis, D sub L S, end sub, plus D sub S V, end sub, close parenthesis, and denominator x\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 2 lambda, times open parenthesis, D sub L S, end sub, plus D sub S V, end sub, close parenthesis, and denominator x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>LS</mtext></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>SV</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 4 lambda, times open parenthesis, D sub L S, end sub, plus D sub S V, end sub, close parenthesis, and denominator x\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 4 lambda, times open parenthesis, D sub L S, end sub, plus D sub S V, end sub, close parenthesis, and denominator x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>LS</mtext></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>D</mi><mtext>SV</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]